data.enText: the floor or ground at the bottom of a doorway , considered as the entrance to a building or room
She stood hesitating on the threshold.
the level at which sth starts to happen or have an effect
He has a low boredom threshold (= he gets bored easily) .
I have a high pain threshold (= I can suffer a lot of pain before I start to react) .

data.chText: 我的收入刚刚超过征税起点。
data.enText: My earnings are just above the tax threshold (= more than the amount at which you start paying tax) .
the point just before a new situation, period of life, etc. begins

data.chText: 她觉得好像就要开始新生活了。
data.enText: She felt as though she was on the threshold of a new life.

tr: a horizontal piece of wood or stone that forms the bottom of a doorway and offers support when passing through a doorway
the entrance (the space in a wall) through which you enter or leave a room or building
the space that a door can close
example: he stuck his head in the doorway

tr: the starting point for a new state or experience

value.def: The threshold of a building or room is the floor in the doorway, or the doorway itself.

example.ex: He stopped at the threshold of the bedroom...
The bride was carried over the threshold.

value.def: A threshold is an amount, level, or limit on a scale. When the threshold is reached, something else happens or changes.

example.ex: She has a low threshold of boredom and needs the constant stimulation of physical activity...
example.tran: 她容易厌倦，需要时常进行活动来刺激一下。

example.ex: The consensus has clearly shifted in favour of raising the nuclear threshold...
example.tran: 显然大家已普遍开始转向支持提高核武器使用的门槛了。

example.ex: Fewer than forty per cent voted — the threshold for results to be valid.
example.tran: 投票的人不到 40%——投票结果无效。

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft N <l>of</l> n, n N

value.tran: (某事发生或改变的)界限，阈，起始点

value.def: If you are on the threshold of something exciting or new, you are about to experience it.

example.ex: We are on the threshold of a new era in astronomy.
example.tran: 我们很快就将迎来天文学的新纪元。

example.ex: ...a lovely girl on the threshold of growing up.
example.tran: 眼看就要长大成人的可爱女孩

value.tran: 在…开端;将要经历;面临着
